dct_description_sm: Running title in margin: Rand-McNally indexed atlas. [Germany, eastern part.]. 398-399. Map of Germany from Berlin and Dresden eastward to present-day Poland. Relief shown by hachures. Ancillary maps: Rhenish-Westphalian industry and mining district -- Berlin, Potsdam and environs. Inset map of northern portion of East Prussia. Index on verso. From: Rand, McNally & Co.'s indexed atlas of the world. Chicago, New York : Rand McNally & Co., [1902?]
